Name: productRequestError

Type: message

Syntax: productRequestError <productID>, <error> 

Summary: Sent by the store when the request for specific product details is unsuccessful.

Introduced: 6.7

OS: ios,android

Platforms: mobile

Example:
on productRequestError pProduct, pError
   "Error:" && pError && "when requesting details for " && pProduct
end productRequestError

Parameters:
productID: The identidier of the product for which the request for details was made.
error (string): A string that describes the error.

Description:
Use the <productRequestError> message to handle unsuccessful request for details of a specific product. 

The message <productRequestError> is sent in response to the <mobileStoreRequestProductDetails> command, when the request is not successful.

